---
title: Sweet Heat Maple Sriracha Chicken with Chili-Roasted Carrots & Brussels Sprouts
description: Sweet and buttery with a touch of heat, our quick and delicious maple-Sriracha sauce elevates juicy pork chops to the next level. Sides of tender roasted carrots seasoned with Korean chili flakes and savory sautéed Brussels sprouts round out this plate that’s sure to tantalize your taste buds for a speedy weeknight dinner.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6643616a38584bf020f8c690-dab189de.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6645065667f64e4e23f5c650-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-heat-maple-sriracha-chicken-6645065667f64e4e23f5c650
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 440 kcal
  fat: 17 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 36 g
  sugar: 22 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 510 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve
any larger carrots lengthwise first).

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @Korean chili flakes{1%tsp}
(use less if you prefer less heat), and @salt{}. Roast on top rack until browned and
tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Sriracha{1%tsp}, @Maple Syrup{2%tbsp}, @Ponzu
Sauce{12%ml}, and @water{2%tbsp}.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

> Swap in chicken or trout for pork. Cook chicken until cooked through,
3-5 minutes per side, or cook trout (skin sides down) until skin is crisp,
5-6 minutes, then flip and cook until opaque and cooked through,
4-6 minutes more.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken cutlets;
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a
#cutting board{} and tent with foil to keep warm.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @Shredded Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce}
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned
and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Add Sriracha mixture; cook, stirring, until
thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} (if sauce seems too thick, stir in @water{1%tsp} at a time).

Turn off heat; stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}
to taste.

Slice chicken crosswise.

> Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing trout!). Chicken is fully cooked when internal
temperature reaches 165°.

Divide chicken, carrots, and Brussels sprouts between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken
and serve.